  <prompt>
    This task is the **Phase 2 closeout GATE** for R5. Phase 2 ships ONLY when this task
    passes. It aggregates and runs the unit + integration tests authored by D2-03 through
    D2-20, fills any test-coverage gaps revealed by the aggregate, performs end-to-end
    Summarize flow verification (both slash command + natural-language tool-call invocation
    paths), verifies the Insights `insights.query` tool consumption (both playbook + RAG
    response paths), runs cross-tool disambiguation tests between `summarize` and
    `insights.query` (NFR-12 quality), measures the cumulative `dotnet publish` BFF size
    delta across the entire R5 series (Phase 1 + Phase 2), runs a transitive-CVE scan, and
    walks through the Phase 2 phase-gating checklist verbatim from `plan.md`.

    Per CLAUDE.md §10 and R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 / §3.7, this task is the binding pre-merge
    enforcement point for the Phase 2 publish-size + test-obligation rules. Per `plan.md`
    Phase 2 phase-gating list, all of the following MUST be green before Phase 3 begins:
      1. End-to-end Summarize flow works on Spaarke Dev (slash command + natural-language
         tool-call both produce identical output per FR-01 + SC-08)
      2. SSE token streaming populates Workspace tab progressively (FR-02 + SC-02)
      3. Context pane file preview + multi-file selection works (FR-05 + SC-04)
      4. Tab persistence + static restoration works (FR-07 + SC-05)
      5. `insights.query` tool registered + both response paths render correctly
         (FR-12 + FR-13 + SC-11)
      6. R5 lead has signed off on Insights contract v1.0 + recorded D1–D6 decisions
         (DR-03 + SC-10 + closure of Insights task 042 sub-task A.5) — confirmed via task 023
      7. Smoke tests pass for both tools against Spaarke Dev synthetic test entities
         (D7 GUIDs from integration brief §8 — verified via task 030)

    Additional cross-tool obligations:
      - Cross-tool disambiguation (NFR-12) — tool routing between `summarize` and
        `insights.query` handles ambiguous prompts gracefully ("summarize this matter" with
        files present vs without; UR-01 resolution path)
      - Cumulative publish-size delta (Phase 1 + Phase 2) ≤ R5 budget (≤+1 MB total;
        target +0.5 MB) per spec NFR-07 + R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6
      - No new HIGH-severity CVE per spec NFR-13 + ADR-029

    This task does NOT add new production BFF or frontend code. It adds tests + verification
    evidence. Single allowed exception: if the aggregate surfaces a missing test that a
    prior D2-* task should have authored, this task fills the gap (recorded in task notes
    with the originating D2-* task ID).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET + frontend test engineer with deep familiarity with the Sprk.Bff.Api test
    project layout, the Spe.Integration.Tests project layout, xUnit conventions, the
    `dotnet publish` size-measurement protocol from `.claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md`,
    the CVE-scan workflow per ADR-029, the asymmetric-registration audit recipe from
    `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` § F.1, and the Spaarke Dev E2E smoke-test
    methodology (Wave D7 synthetic test entities from the Insights integration brief §8).
    Operator of Spaarke Dev smoke tests for chat-agent tool invocations + SSE consumption
    verification + cross-tool disambiguation observations.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Phase 2 GATE is GREEN. Concretely:
      - Every unit + integration test file authored by tasks 010–030 is present + passing;
        coverage gaps are filled if any are found
      - E2E Summarize flow verified on Spaarke Dev across BOTH invocation paths
        (`/summarize` slash → direct endpoint AND natural-language → `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`
        via `SprkChatAgent`); output schemas identical per SC-08
      - SSE `FieldDelta` streaming populates `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` progressively;
        new Workspace tab opens additively (FR-06); tab persists + restores statically (FR-07)
      - Context pane `FilePreviewContextWidget` renders single + multi-file with click-to-swap
        (FR-05); "Summarize this only" per-file affordance produces additive tab (FR-08)
      - `insights.query` tool registered; smoke tests against Spaarke Dev synthetic test
        entities (matter `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`, project
        `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`, invoice `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`)
        confirm BOTH response paths (playbook structured envelope rendered via
        `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` static mode; RAG path rendered with citation-grounded
        prose + `[n]` tokens) work correctly
      - Cross-tool disambiguation tests show acceptable routing on ambiguous prompts
        (UR-01 resolution recorded; any misroute observations flagged for Phase 3 follow-up)
      - Cumulative Phase 1 + Phase 2 BFF publish-size delta ≤ R5 budget (≤+1 MB; target
        +0.5 MB) vs pre-R5 baseline (~45.65 MB → ceiling target ≤46.15 MB; hard ceiling 60 MB)
      - No new HIGH-severity CVE in `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`
      - R5 lead sign-off on Insights contract v1.0 confirmed (from task 023 closeout)
      - `TASK-INDEX.md` reflects: 031 ✅; Phase 2 status flipped to ✅; `current-task.md`
        reset to next pending task (task 040 D3-01 `/analyze` proof point)
  </goal>

