  <constraints>
    <constraint source="plan.md Phase 2 gating">Phase 2 ships only when ALL of: E2E Summarize works on Spaarke Dev (slash + natural-language identical output); SSE streaming populates Workspace tab progressively; Context pane file preview + multi-file selection works; tab persistence + static restoration works; `insights.query` registered + both response paths render correctly; R5 lead sign-off on Insights contract v1.0 + D1–D6 decisions recorded; smoke tests pass against Spaarke Dev synthetic test entities. This task is the binding gate.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-01 + SC-08">Both `/summarize` (slash command → direct endpoint) AND natural-language summarize requests (LLM tool-call → agent tool) MUST produce identical `DocumentAnalysisResult` shape. Verify by invoking both paths with same files; compare outputs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-02 + SC-02">Summary output MUST stream progressively via `FieldDelta` SSE events; `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` renders each field progressively (ChatGPT/Claude-style; NOT plop). Verify by SSE event capture in browser DevTools.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-05 + SC-04">Context pane MUST render single-file preview AND multi-file list with click-to-swap. Per-file 3-dot menu reuses existing `DocumentRowMenu` (aiSummary + toggleWorkspace + findSimilar actions).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-07 + SC-05">After streaming completes, browser refresh MUST restore the summary tab statically via persisted `ISummarizeResult`; NO re-streaming.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12 + FR-13 + SC-11">`insights.query` tool MUST be registered on `SprkChatAgent`; both response paths (playbook structured envelope + RAG citation-grounded prose) MUST render correctly against Spaarke Dev Wave D7 synthetic test entities (matter `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`, project `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`, invoice `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07">Cumulative R5 BFF publish-size delta ≤ +1 MB compressed (target +0.5 MB); total ≤ 47 MB compressed (current pre-R5 baseline ~45.65 MB; NFR-01 ceiling 60 MB). Phase 2 cumulative measurement is THIS task's verification responsibility.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-12">Tool descriptions for `summarize` and `insights.query` MUST be non-overlapping and scope-explicit. Cross-tool disambiguation tests MUST exercise ambiguous prompts ("summarize this matter" with files vs without) and document routing observations. Per UR-01 resolution path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-13">No new HIGH-severity CVE permitted. `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` MUST be clean before Phase 2 closes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-14">Test coverage — new endpoints, services, widgets MUST have corresponding tests; endpoints mapping unconditionally MUST have unconditional service registration (R5 services unconditionally registered per ADR-018 Flag Scope Discipline; verified at Phase 1 close).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene item 6">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. This task is the binding verification of the test-update obligation for Phase 2 BFF changes (tasks 012, 014, 015, 024, 025, 026, 027, 028, 029).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 BFF Hygiene item 4">Every BFF-touching task measures publish size. This task aggregates the cumulative Phase 1 + Phase 2 delta and is the binding per-phase verification point for Phase 2.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec DR-03 + SC-10">R5 lead sign-off on Insights `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 + 6 contract-review decisions (D1–D6) recorded in §10 review log MUST be complete (closure of Insights task 042 sub-task A.5). Verified via task 023 closeout; confirmed here as Phase 2 gate prerequisite.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. All Phase 2 services unconditionally registered. Asymmetric-registration audit clean per task 009 Phase 1 closeout; Phase 2 changes inherit this discipline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — framework-dependent linux-x64; report absolute size + diff vs baseline; ≥+5 MB single-task / phase delta requires explicit escalation; ≥55 MB cumulative requires architecture review; ≥60 MB is HARD STOP.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">R5 budget ≤ +1 MB total (target +0.5 MB). Phase 1 should consume well under half; Phase 2 lands the remainder. If cumulative delta is ≥ +1 MB: escalate per CLAUDE.md §6 BEFORE marking the gate green.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7">Endpoints map unconditionally → services register unconditionally. Verified at Phase 1 close; this task confirms Phase 2 BFF additions (new `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize` endpoint per task 014) followed the same discipline.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">This task adds tests + verification evidence ONLY. No new production BFF or frontend code unless required to fill a gap surfaced by the aggregate run. Any gap-fill code MUST be recorded in task notes with cross-reference to the originating D2-* task.</constraint>
  </constraints>

