    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Phase 2 BFF test aggregate run" location="tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/">
        `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj --logger
        "trx;LogFileName=phase2-aggregate.trx"`. Examine output for new test files created
        by D2-03..D2-19. Expected new test files (locations TBD per each D2-* task POML):
        `SessionSummarizeOrchestratorTests.cs` (task 012), `SummarizeSessionEndpointTests.cs`
        (task 014), `InvokeSummarizePlaybookToolTests.cs` (task 015),
        `InsightsQueryToolHandlerTests.cs` (task 024), `InsightsSubjectResolutionTests.cs`
        (task 025), `InsightsResponseRendererTests.cs` (task 026 — frontend),
        `InsightsErrorCodeHandlingTests.cs` (task 029). Confirm presence + green status.
        Fill gaps if found.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Phase 2 integration test run" location="tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/">
        `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ --logger
        "trx;LogFileName=phase2-integration.trx"`. Existing fixture
        (`IntegrationTestFixture.cs`) provides Spaarke Dev test-host. Expected new files:
        Summarize end-to-end test exercising new endpoint + agent-tool path;
        `insights.query` tool consumption test against synthetic test entities.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="E2E Summarize flow verification (both paths)" location="Spaarke Dev BFF + SpaarkeAi shell">
        (a) Slash command path: open SpaarkeAi on Spaarke Dev; upload sample file (within
            R4 25 MB cap + MIME allow-list per docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md);
            invoke `/summarize`; verify SSE delta events stream into new Workspace tab via
            `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` progressively; final `ISummarizeResult`
            persists; refresh restores tab statically.
        (b) Natural-language path: same setup; type "summarize the file I uploaded"
            (natural language, no slash); verify `SprkChatAgent` tool-calls
            `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`; verify output schema identical to slash-command
            path per SC-08.
        (c) Capture SSE event log from DevTools + screenshot references for both paths.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Insights tool consumption verification (both response paths)" location="Spaarke Dev BFF + SpaarkeAi shell">
        (a) Playbook path: invoke `insights.query` with `forceMode` = playbook-classifier
            target (e.g., `predict-matter-cost@v1`) against matter
            `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`; verify response renders via
            `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` in static mode (v1.0 fallback) OR progressively
            via SSE (v1.1 when Wave F shipped); verify confidence badge per FR-15.
        (b) RAG path: invoke natural-language entity-scoped question without
            `forceMode`; verify response renders as citation-grounded prose with `[n]`
            tokens; verify clickable citations (v1.1) OR display-name-only (v1.0); verify
            x-correlation-id propagated end-to-end via App Insights / Kusto lookup.
        (c) Decline + empty-result cases: trigger with low-content matter / out-of-scope
            query; verify decline state renders `SuggestedActions`; empty-results renders
            "couldn't find anything" hint (not empty answer).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Cross-tool disambiguation tests (NFR-12 / UR-01)" location="Spaarke Dev SpaarkeAi shell">
        Exercise ambiguous prompts that COULD match both `summarize` and `insights.query`:
        (a) "summarize this matter" WITH files uploaded → expected route: `summarize`
            (file-scoped wins)
        (b) "summarize this matter" WITHOUT files uploaded → expected route:
            `insights.query` (entity-scoped wins; or interjection per FR-03 if no entity
            context either)
        (c) "what's the predicted cost on this matter?" → expected route: `insights.query`
        (d) "what's in the file I just uploaded?" → expected route: ad-hoc grounded RAG
            via session-scoped retrieval (FR-09); NOT `summarize` unless user invoked it.
        Record observations. Misroutes are NOT a Phase 2 blocker (UR-01 resolution path
        permits Phase 3 follow-up); document for Phase 3 if observed.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Cumulative publish-size measurement (Phase 1 + Phase 2)" location=".claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md § 'BFF Publish-Size Per-Task Verification Rule (NFR-01)'">
        Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
        Compress and measure. Compare against pre-R5 baseline (~45.65 MB recorded in task
        002's pre-Phase-1 evidence + verified at task 009 Phase 1 closeout). Cumulative
        delta = current_size − pre_R5_baseline. Budget: ≤ +1 MB total; target +0.5 MB.
        Report in task notes using the binding format: `BFF Hygiene §10 + NFR-01 verified:
        Phase 2 publish size = X MB, R5 cumulative delta = +Y MB, baseline = 45.65 MB,
        ceiling = 60 MB compressed, no new HIGH CVEs.`
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="CVE scan recipe" location="CLAUDE.md §10 item 5 + ADR-029">
        `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` from repo root. Filter for
        HIGH severity. Compare against the pre-R5 baseline + Phase 1 close baseline (both
        in task 009 evidence). Any NEW HIGH MUST block Phase 2 close until either resolved
        (package upgrade) or explicitly accepted (ADR amendment).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="R5 lead sign-off verification" location="task 023 closeout + projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md §10">
        Confirm task 023 marked ✅ in TASK-INDEX. Confirm Insights contract §10 review log
        shows R5 lead sign-off + 6 decisions (D1–D6) recorded. Confirm Insights task 042
        sub-task A.5 closed via cross-project coordination doc reference. This is a binding
        Phase 2 prerequisite per spec DR-03 + SC-10.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Phase 2 phase-gating walk-through" location="plan.md Phase 2 § 'Phase gating'">
        Walk verbatim through each of the 7 phase-gating items from plan.md (E2E Summarize;
        SSE streaming; Context pane preview; tab persistence; insights.query both paths;
        R5 lead sign-off; smoke tests). For each: record evidence (test result, smoke log,
        screenshot reference, contract §10 link). All 7 MUST be GREEN before marking the
        gate ✅.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase 2 of R5 ships the chat-driven Summarize vertical slice AND the Insights tool
      integration — together making R5's chat surface the operational **Spaarke Assistant**
      with two coexisting AI tool capabilities. Shipping Phase 2 in a degraded state
      (failing E2E flow, misrouting tool calls, broken cross-tool disambiguation, oversized
      publish, undetected CVE) would compound into Phase 3 polish + the platform-extension
      proof point. Per CLAUDE.md §10 the BFF binding rule REQUIRES per-task publish-size
      verification AND a phase-level verification at the close of every phase that adds to
      the BFF. Per R5 CLAUDE.md §3.7 the test obligation requires every D2-* task to have
      authored its own tests — but as with Phase 1, an aggregate verification gate runs at
      phase close to catch gaps.

      Cross-tool disambiguation (NFR-12 / UR-01) is the highest novel risk in Phase 2.
      Phase 1 platform-extension work introduced the `summarize` chat-agent tool; Phase 2
      adds the `insights.query` chat-agent tool. Both LLM tool descriptions must scope
      cleanly (`summarize` = file-scoped, session-scoped; `insights.query` = entity-scoped,
      knowledge-scoped). Misroute risk is medium per plan.md High-Risk Items. The gate
      includes explicit disambiguation tests + observation recording for Phase 3 follow-up.

      The R5 lead sign-off prerequisite (DR-03) is operator-led and was verified during
      task 023 (Pre-G6 gate). This task confirms task 023 remains ✅ and the §10 review log
      still reflects the 6 D-decisions.

      Insights Wave F status: Wave F (v1.1 SSE + clickable citations) is in flight in
      parallel via Claude Code on branch `work/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2-wave-f`. R5
      Phase 2 ships with graceful v1.0 fallback per NFR-11. If Wave F has shipped by the
      time this task runs, R5 consumes v1.1; otherwise v1.0 fallback engages and Phase 2
      ships in the degraded-but-functional state per plan.md High-Risk Items.

      Cost of skipping this gate: a Phase 3 task discovers a Phase 2 regression in flight,
      blocking the `/analyze` proof point that validates the platform-extension claim (SC-19)
      and forcing a rebase across the polish-phase deliverables.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="010" status="not-started">D2-01 `sprk_analysisaction` "Summarize Document for Chat" seed — verify deployed + visible on Spaarke Dev</dependency>
      <dependency task="011" status="not-started">D2-02 `sprk_analysisplaybook` configuration — verify linked to D2-01 action</dependency>
      <dependency task="012" status="not-started">D2-03 `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` — verify tests + unconditional registration</dependency>
