  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL Declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`. Output
      the mandatory RIGOR LEVEL declaration per root CLAUDE.md §8:
      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Phase 2 gate task aggregating unit + integration tests + E2E Summarize
                  verification (both invocation paths) + Insights tool verification (both
                  response paths) + cross-tool disambiguation + cumulative publish-size +
                  CVE scan + R5-lead-sign-off confirmation across 21 dependency tasks;
                  blocking gate before Phase 3.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 0 through 10 below.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>

    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Dependency Validation">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm tasks 010–030 ALL show ✅. If ANY show 🔲 or 🔄,
      STOP and report the gate cannot run yet. Read `current-task.md` to confirm 031 is the
      next pending task. Read `notes/phase-1-closeout-report.md` to extract the pre-R5
      publish-size baseline + Phase 1 cumulative delta + Phase 1 CVE baseline. Read each
      D2-* task's POML to extract:
        (a) the test file path(s) the task was supposed to author;
        (b) the per-task publish-size delta the task recorded in its notes (for BFF tasks
            only — Dataverse seeds + frontend tasks contribute 0 MB);
        (c) any deferred / open items the task flagged for Phase 2 close;
        (d) for tasks 024/025/026/027/028/029 (Insights consumption suite): the v1.1 vs
            v1.0 status at task completion.
      Aggregate the per-task publish-size deltas into the expected cumulative Phase 2
      delta (informational; the authoritative measurement is Step 5 below).
    </step>

    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract:
        (a) the Phase 2 phase-gating list from `plan.md` (7 items);
        (b) the publish-size protocol from `.claude/constraints/azure-deployment.md`;
        (c) the test-update obligation from CLAUDE.md §10 item 6;
        (d) the integration brief §5.1 error matrix (12 codes) — referenced for E2E
            verification of task 029's coverage;
        (e) the Wave D7 synthetic test entity GUIDs from integration brief §8 — used by
            Step 7 Insights tool consumption verification.
      Read the R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6 + §3.7 in full. Read `notes/insights-r2-coordination.md`
      §8 changelog to capture current Wave F status (informs v1.0-vs-v1.1 verification
      branch in Step 7).
    </step>

    <step order="3" name="R5 Lead Sign-Off Verification (Phase 2 prerequisite)">
      (a) Confirm task 023 (D2-13) status is ✅ in TASK-INDEX.
      (b) Read task 023's closeout notes — confirm Insights contract
          `projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` §10
          review log shows R5 lead sign-off + 6 D-decisions (D1–D6) recorded.
      (c) Confirm Insights task 042 sub-task A.5 closure is referenced.
      (d) If ANY of the above are missing: STOP and escalate per CLAUDE.md §6 — Phase 2
          gate cannot close without DR-03 + SC-10 satisfied.
      Record verification outcome in task notes with file references / timestamps.
    </step>

    <step order="4" name="Build BFF + Aggregate Unit + Integration Test Runs">
      (a) Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — MUST succeed with zero errors
          and no new warnings vs Phase 1 close baseline. Capture warning delta.
      (b) Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests.csproj --logger
          "trx;LogFileName=phase2-aggregate.trx"`. MUST show zero failures.
      (c) Run `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ --logger
          "trx;LogFileName=phase2-integration.trx"`. MUST show zero failures.
      (d) For each D2-* task that authored tests, verify the expected test file(s) (per
          the POML's `&lt;outputs&gt;` section) exist in the appropriate test project and
          contain at least one passing test per FR/NFR the task targeted. If a test file
          is missing or under-covered, RECORD the gap in task notes.
      (e) For frontend tasks (013, 017, 018, 020, 021, 022, 026, 027, 028): run the
          relevant component test suites (`npm test` in the appropriate package); confirm
          zero failures.
      (f) If gaps surface: AUTHOR the missing tests in this task (record the originating
          D2-* task ID for traceability). Re-run the aggregate. MUST converge to green.
    </step>

    <step order="5" name="Cumulative Publish-Size Measurement (Phase 1 + Phase 2)">
      (a) Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
      (b) Measure compressed size of `deploy/api-publish/` (zip or `Compress-Archive` then
          inspect `.Length`).
      (c) Compute the cumulative R5 delta = current_compressed_size −
          pre_R5_baseline_compressed_size (per Phase 1 closeout recorded baseline,
          originally from task 002). Also compute the Phase-2-only delta = current_size −
          Phase_1_close_size (per task 009 evidence).
      (d) Verify: cumulative R5 delta ≤ +1 MB (budget) AND ideally ≤ +0.5 MB (target). If
          ≥ +0.5 MB but ≤ +1 MB: still inside budget; flag in PR description per R5
          CLAUDE.md §3.6. If ≥ +1 MB: ESCALATE per CLAUDE.md §6 — do NOT mark the gate
          green.
      (e) Report in task notes using the binding format: `BFF Hygiene §10 + NFR-01
          verified: Phase 2 publish size = X MB, R5 cumulative delta = +Y MB,
          Phase-2-only delta = +Z MB, baseline = 45.65 MB, ceiling = 60 MB compressed,
          no new HIGH CVEs.`
    </step>

    <step order="6" name="CVE Transitive Scan">
      Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` from repo root. Capture
      full output. Filter for entries marked HIGH severity. Compare against the Phase 1
      close baseline (in task 009 evidence) + the pre-R5 baseline. MUST be zero NEW HIGH.
      Record the full HIGH list (existing + new) in task notes. If new HIGH surfaces:
      either upgrade the offending package or ESCALATE per CLAUDE.md §6.
    </step>

    <step order="7" name="E2E Summarize Flow Verification (BOTH invocation paths) on Spaarke Dev">
      Per FR-01 + FR-02 + FR-06 + FR-07 + SC-01 + SC-02 + SC-03 + SC-05 + SC-08:
      (a) **Slash command path**: Open SpaarkeAi on Spaarke Dev. Upload sample file
          (within R4 25 MB cap + MIME allow-list per docs/standards/CHAT-ATTACHMENT-POLICY.md).
          Invoke `/summarize`. Verify:
            - SSE delta events stream into new Workspace tab via
              `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` progressively (NOT a final-result plop)
            - Tab opens additively (other tabs untouched per FR-06 + SC-03)
            - Final `ISummarizeResult` persists to workspace tab state
            - Browser refresh restores tab statically (no re-streaming) per FR-07 + SC-05
            - Capture DevTools SSE event log + screenshot references for evidence
      (b) **Natural-language path**: Same setup; instead of `/summarize`, type "summarize
          the file I uploaded" (natural language). Verify:
            - `SprkChatAgent` tool-calls `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`
            - Output schema identical to slash-command path per SC-08 (compare
              `DocumentAnalysisResult` JSON structurally)
            - Capture DevTools event log + final-output reference
      (c) **Multi-file path** (FR-04 + SC-04): Upload 3+ files. Invoke `/summarize`.
          Verify multi-file deterministic interjection ("I'll provide a combined summary
          for the files you uploaded") appears once before streaming begins. Verify
          Context pane shows list of file cards + click-to-swap. Verify combined summary
          populates `fileHighlights[]`.
      (d) **Prompt-first path** (FR-03): Open fresh session with no files; invoke
          `/summarize` first; verify deterministic interjection ("Upload the file(s) you'd
          like me to summarize") appears; upload file; verify subsequent flow completes.
      (e) **Per-file affordance path** (FR-08 + SC-06): Upload 2+ files; click "Summarize
          this only" on file card 2; verify new additive tab opens; prior tab preserved.
      (f) **Decline-to-find path** (FR-11 + SC-09): Upload empty/tiny file; invoke
          `/summarize`; verify `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` renders decline state
          distinctly with `SuggestedActions` (not hallucinated summary).
      (g) **General grounded Q&A path** (FR-09 + SC-07): With files in session, ask
          "are there litigation risks?"; verify response cites session-file chunks via
          `RagSearchOptions.sessionId` filter (not knowledge-index citations).
      Record evidence references (DevTools captures, screenshots, log query refs) in task
      notes for each sub-step.
    </step>

    <step order="8" name="Insights Tool Verification (BOTH response paths) on Spaarke Dev">
      Per FR-12 + FR-13 + FR-14 + FR-15 + FR-16 + FR-17 + SC-11 + SC-12 + SC-13 + SC-14 +
      SC-15 + SC-16 + SC-17:
      (a) **Playbook response path**: Invoke `insights.query` with `forceMode` set (via
          `/ask-insights` slash command path) against matter
          `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`. Verify:
            - Response renders via `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` in static mode (v1.0)
              OR progressively via SSE (v1.1 if Wave F shipped — check coordination doc §8)
            - Confidence badge per FR-15: appears when `confidence < 0.6`; absent
              otherwise; threshold configurable
            - Capture screenshot + structured-envelope reference
      (b) **RAG response path**: Invoke natural-language entity-scoped question (e.g.,
          "what are the key risks for this matter?") against same matter; verify:
            - Response renders as citation-grounded prose with `[n]` tokens via
              `InsightsResponseRenderer` RAG sub-renderer
            - Clickable citations (v1.1 `href` present) open source in
              `FilePreviewContextWidget` via PaneEventBus `context.context_update` event
            - v1.0 fallback (when `href: null` or absent): citations render as
              display-name-only per FR-14 + NFR-11 + SC-13
            - x-correlation-id propagated end-to-end per FR-17 + SC-16; verify via App
              Insights / Kusto lookup with the correlation ID surfaced in DevTools network
              tab
      (c) **Decline + empty-result paths**: Trigger with low-content matter or
          out-of-scope query; verify:
            - Decline state renders `answer` + `envelope.SuggestedActions` as plain text
              per integration brief §5 + FR-13
            - Empty-results renders "couldn't find anything" hint (not empty answer)
      (d) **Project + invoice verification**: Repeat playbook path with project
          `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4` and invoice
          `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`; confirm responses usable per
          integration brief §8 SME walkthrough criteria.
      (e) **Error code coverage**: Verify task 030 smoke tests captured all 12 error
          codes per integration brief §5.1; confirm per-code UX rendered correctly with
          no raw stack traces / document content leaking per FR-16 + SC-15.
      Record evidence references in task notes for each sub-step.
    </step>

    <step order="9" name="Cross-Tool Disambiguation Tests (NFR-12 / UR-01)">
      Exercise ambiguous prompts that could match both `summarize` AND `insights.query`:
      (a) "summarize this matter" WITH files uploaded → expected route: `summarize`
          (file-scoped wins per FR-01 + NFR-12 tool description)
      (b) "summarize this matter" WITHOUT files uploaded → expected route:
          `insights.query` (entity-scoped wins) OR prompt-first interjection per FR-03 if
          no entity context resolvable
      (c) "what's the predicted cost on this matter?" → expected route: `insights.query`
      (d) "what's in the file I just uploaded?" → expected route: ad-hoc grounded RAG via
          `RagSearchOptions.sessionId` filter (FR-09); NOT `summarize` unless user
          explicitly invokes it
      (e) "tell me about this matter" → expected route: `insights.query` (entity-scoped
          generic question)
      For each prompt: record the LLM's tool-call decision + observation of whether
      routing matched expectation. Misroutes are NOT a Phase 2 blocker (UR-01 resolution
      path permits Phase 3 follow-up — tool description refinement + explicit "did you
      mean..." clarification). Document each misroute observation for Phase 3 backlog with
      enough detail to refine tool descriptions during Phase 3.
      Record disambiguation matrix in task notes:
        | Prompt | Expected route | Actual route | Pass/Observe |
    </step>

    <step order="10" name="Phase 2 Phase-Gating Checklist Walk-Through">
      Walk verbatim through each of the 7 phase-gating items from `plan.md` Phase 2
      header. For each, record GREEN / RED + evidence link:
      (i)   E2E Summarize works on Spaarke Dev (slash + natural-language identical
            output per FR-01 + SC-08) → evidence: Step 7 (a) + (b) captures
      (ii)  SSE token streaming populates Workspace tab progressively (FR-02 + SC-02) →
            evidence: Step 7 (a) DevTools SSE event log
      (iii) Context pane file preview + multi-file selection works (FR-05 + SC-04) →
            evidence: Step 7 (c) + (e) screenshot references
      (iv)  Tab persistence + static restoration works (FR-07 + SC-05) → evidence:
            Step 7 (a) refresh-restoration screenshot
      (v)   `insights.query` tool registered + both response paths render correctly
            (FR-12 + FR-13 + SC-11) → evidence: Step 8 (a) + (b) captures
      (vi)  R5 lead has signed off on Insights contract v1.0 + recorded D1–D6 decisions
            (DR-03 + SC-10; closes Insights task 042 sub-task A.5) → evidence: Step 3
            verification
      (vii) Smoke tests pass for both tools against Spaarke Dev synthetic test entities
            (Wave D7 GUIDs per integration brief §8) → evidence: task 030 closeout + Step
            8 (d) verification
      ALL 7 MUST be GREEN. ANY RED MUST be remediated before marking the gate ✅.
    </step>

    <step order="10.5" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and confirm each is testable +
      passing. Record evidence per criterion in task notes.
    </step>

    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against any new test files authored by this task (gap-fill
      tests, if any). Run `adr-check` skill against new test files + any module changes;
      verify ADR-018 (no new flags — Phase 2 inherits), ADR-029 (publish hygiene),
      ADR-010 (DI minimalism — Phase 2 services registered inside `AnalysisServicesModule`
      per task 014), ADR-013 (BFF-only — R5 is Zone B consumer of Insights HTTP contract;
      no Insights internals injected per task 024/025 closeout), ADR-014 (tenant isolation
      — session-files index + Insights filtering preserve `tenantId` per task 030 smoke
      tests), ADR-028 (Auth v2 — new endpoint per task 014; no token snapshots),
      ADR-030 (PaneEventBus additive — Phase 2 added 5 event types within existing 4
      channels per task 016). Both gates MUST pass before marking the task ✅.
    </step>

    <step order="11" name="Phase 2 Closeout + TASK-INDEX Update">
      (a) Update task 031 POML status to `complete`. Record actual-effort.
      (b) Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 031 🔲 → ✅. Flip Phase 2 phase status to ✅.
      (c) Update `current-task.md` to reset to the next pending task per CLAUDE.md §7.
          Next-up per TASK-INDEX is task 040 (D3-01 `/analyze` configuration-only proof
          point — validates SC-19 platform-extension claim). Set `current-task.md`
          accordingly.
      (d) Author the Phase 2 closeout report at
          `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/phase-2-closeout-report.md`
          containing: aggregate unit + integration test result; E2E Summarize verification
          (both paths) evidence; Insights tool verification (both response paths) evidence;
          cross-tool disambiguation matrix + Phase 3 backlog items (if any); cumulative
          publish-size measurement (Phase 1 + Phase 2); CVE scan result; R5 lead sign-off
          confirmation; Phase 2 phase-gating walk-through outcome (7 items GREEN); any
          gap-fill tests authored by this task; list of carry-over items (if any).
      (e) Update `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md`
          §8 changelog with the Phase 2 close entry (timestamp + reference to the closeout
          report + Wave F status at Phase 2 close — informs Phase 3 reading).
      (f) Report task completion + Phase 2 GATE GREEN declaration.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
