    <criterion testable="true">Frontend component test suites (for tasks 013, 017, 018, 020, 021, 022, 026, 027, 028) complete with zero failures (`npm test` in each relevant package).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">E2E Summarize flow on Spaarke Dev: BOTH invocation paths (slash command → direct endpoint `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{id}/summarize` AND natural-language → `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` via `SprkChatAgent`) produce identical `DocumentAnalysisResult` output schema per SC-08; SSE `FieldDelta` events stream progressively into `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`; new Workspace tab opens additively (others untouched); tab persists + restores statically after refresh; multi-file combined-summary interjection appears once; prompt-first interjection works; per-file "Summarize this only" produces additive tab; decline-to-find renders distinctly; general grounded Q&A cites session-file chunks via `sessionId`-filtered RAG.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Insights `insights.query` tool on Spaarke Dev: BOTH response paths render correctly — playbook path renders structured envelope via `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (static mode for v1.0; progressive SSE for v1.1 if Wave F shipped); RAG path renders citation-grounded prose with `[n]` clickable citations (v1.1) OR display-name-only (v1.0 fallback); decline + empty-result cases render distinctly; confidence badge appears for `<0.6` and absent otherwise; x-correlation-id propagates end-to-end (verified via App Insights / Kusto); all 3 Wave D7 synthetic test entities (matter `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`, project `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`, invoice `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`) produce usable responses; all 12 error codes from integration brief §5.1 verified per task 030 closeout with no raw stack traces / document content leaking.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Cross-tool disambiguation (NFR-12 / UR-01): 5 ambiguous prompts tested; routing observations recorded in disambiguation matrix; misroutes (if any) documented for Phase 3 backlog (not a Phase 2 blocker per UR-01 resolution path).</criterion>
